The paper deals with the problem of finding a drawing of a graph in the plane with minimum number of edge crossings, which is a central problem in topological graph theory. This problem is closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG), as it involves geometric representations of graphs. The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve randomized algorithms and approximation algorithms, which are common in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem also has connections to graph theory (cs.GT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA), as finding the minimum crossing number involves solving optimization problems and computing numerical approximations.
